Australia, N.Z. Stocks: BHP, James Hardie, Mirvac, Rio Tinto

-- B y   S h a n i   R a j a
-- 
2011-10-03T05:41:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/australia-n-z-stocks-bhp-james-hardie-mirvac-rio-tinto.html
Australia ’s S&P/ASX 200 Index dropped
2.8 percent to 3,897 at the 4:10 p.m. close of trading in Sydney.
The gauge, which just completed its second consecutive quarterly
decline, has lost 18 percent this year.  New Zealand’s NZX 50 Index declined 0.8 percent to 3,315.74
at the 5 p.m. close in Wellington. The gauge just completed its
first quarterly decline in five, and has risen 0.2 percent this
year.  The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  Australia:  Mining stocks: A measure of primary metals traded in  London 
fell 3.4 percent on Sept. 30, and copper futures slumped as much
as 4.9 percent today.  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  , the world’s No. 1 mining
company, fell 2.5 percent to A$34.15.  Rio Tinto  Group (RIO AU),
the world’s second-largest mining company by sales, declined 4.1
percent to A$59.30, the lowest in two years.  Oil stocks: Crude oil for November delivery fell 3.5
percent in  New York  on Sept. 30, and as much as 1.6 percent
today.  Woodside Petroleum Ltd. (WPL)  , Australia’s second-
biggest oil and gas producer, sank 2.7 percent to A$31.62.
 Santos Ltd. (STO)  , Australia’s third-largest oil and gas
producer, lost 2.6 percent to A$11.08.        James Hardie Industries SE (JHX)   sank 3.5 percent to
A$5.55. The building-materials supplier that gets almost 70
percent of sales from the U.S. dropped after U.S. consumer
spending slowed as incomes unexpectedly dropped.  Brambles Ltd. (BXB)  , which gets almost half its revenue
from the Americas, retreated 2.8 percent to A$6.29.  Mirvac Group (MGR)   dropped 0.9 percent to A$1.14. The
property and development group said it entered into a binding
agreement to sell a 50 percent stake in the Hoxton Distribution
Park for A$97.4 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Shani Raja in Sydney at 
 sraja4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 John McCluskey  at 
 j.mccluskey@bloomberg.net . 